Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.84,0:00:05.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The inside of the heart is like a mystery, but the shining stars and sparkling snow illuminate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.51,0:00:08.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The tension is rising in this courtroom scene,\Nwhat will happen to the couple's case?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.39,0:00:14.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who sees the single truth, with the body of a child, his mind that of an adult, his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.86,0:01:53.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran's mother, Attorney Kisaki, has gone up against the prosecutor, the "Madonna of the courtroom," Kujo Reiko, in the Usami Shinji case.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.87,0:02:01.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one holding the key to Usami's alibi\Nis none other than uncle himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.05,0:02:10.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, he was suddenly called as a witness for the prosecution.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.07,0:02:20.74,Signs,,0,0,0,,The Courtroom Showdown! Kisaki vs. Kogorou
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.07,0:02:20.74,Signs,,0,0,0,,(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.28,0:02:23.95,Signs,,0,0,0,,Tokyo District Court
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.70,0:02:40.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, where were you and what were you doing the night of the crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.84,0:02:46.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was in the Haido district, drinking sake at the Mimasu Bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.01,0:02:51.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There, you got so drunk that you fell asleep, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.39,0:02:52.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.32,0:02:55.90,Signs,,0,0,0,,Kujoo Reiko (33), Prosecutor
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.68,0:02:55.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you remember what time you woke up?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.39,0:02:57.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was at 9:25 P.M.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.90,0:03:00.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did you know the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.90,0:03:08.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While I was sleeping, I got a call on my cellphone, and the bar owner woke me up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.49,0:03:12.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And my cellphone's clock read 9:25.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.91,0:03:17.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, were there any other customers?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.04,0:03:27.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was the only one, but my signal wasn't very good\Nso I tried to exit the bar as a man came in.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.26,0:03:30.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you remember that man's face?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.68,0:03:35.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, it was the defendant, Usami Shinji.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.23,0:03:36.19,Signs,,0,0,0,,Usami Shinji (40), Suspect
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.73,0:03:40.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei, what could this mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.98,0:03:43.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would the prosecution bring up the defendant's alibi?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.48,0:03:49.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know... They must have something planned, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.99,0:03:55.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It sure was a surprise that Dad would testify for the\Nprosecution, but I guess he's still on Mom's side.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.04,0:03:57.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.50,0:04:00.08,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}For now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.75,0:04:03.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I am through with questioning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.63,0:04:06.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Very well then, the defense may begin cross-examination.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.21,0:04:07.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.38,0:04:14.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, Mori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, how long was the defendant, Usami, at Mimasu?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.39,0:04:18.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was there for about half an hour, that is, until about 10 P.M.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.77,0:04:28.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you're saying that at the time of the murder, between 9:30 and 10:00 P.M., he was at Mimasu?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.65,0:04:30.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess that's how it'd be.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.74,0:04:34.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.58,0:04:38.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then we will escort the...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.73,0:04:38.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your Honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.37,0:04:41.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,May I ask just a few more questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.79,0:04:43.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Very well then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.79,0:04:45.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.63,0:04:53.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you stated earlier that you fell asleep in the bar and the hostess woke you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.29,0:04:55.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.35,0:04:59.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where was your phone at that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.10,0:05:00.72,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Here it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.23,0:05:09.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, it was in the pocket of my jacket, which was hanging on the coat hanger on the side of the counter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.20,0:05:19.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, someone could very well have changed the time on your phone while you were asleep, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.37,0:05:23.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For example, the bar's hostess.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.54,0:05:24.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's absurd!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.49,0:05:25.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Objection!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.54,0:05:29.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the prosecution is stating is pure conjecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.55,0:05:33.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I ask that the prosecution back up their accusation with facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.47,0:05:35.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.39,0:05:46.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, Your Honor, I'd like to call the owner of Mimasu to the stand, Kameda Masako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, as a witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.27,0:05:50.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She got us...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.86,0:05:52.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.03,0:05:56.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To be so caught up with the alibi and to overlook\Nthis possibility, it was my miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.54,0:06:05.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's happening, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.00,0:06:11.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So long as the cell phone wasn't in Uncle's hands, the alibi doesn't hold up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.59,0:06:24.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words while Uncle was asleep, someone could have changed the time on his cell phone and called him to get him to check the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.35,0:06:31.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, once Uncle took his eyes off of the phone again, you would just have to change it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.90,0:06:34.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a possibility that the bar hostess could have done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.40,0:06:36.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.45,0:06:49.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, just like you, Kisaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} believed that the couple didn't get along, and overlooked the possibility that the alibi was fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.67,0:06:52.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.26,0:07:02.97,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Kameda Masako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, on the night of the crime, did you\Ntamper with the clock on Mouri Kogorou's cell phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.73,0:07:02.69,Signs,,0,0,0,,Kameda Masako (38), Usami's ex-wife
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.69,0:07:09.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.23,0:07:15.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me remind you that if you give false testimony, you can be charged with perjury.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.95,0:07:17.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Masako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.87,0:07:24.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's as... it's as the prosecutor said.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.50,0:07:32.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you admit to tampering with the cell phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.84,0:07:33.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.67,0:07:41.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, what time did Usami actually cross paths with Mouri and showed up at your bar?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.05,0:07:47.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I added 30 minutes, so I expect it to have been 9:55.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.02,0:07:53.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your Honor, the crime scene and the bar are about a 10-minute walk away...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.07,0:07:57.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,which means the defendant had more than enough time to commit the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.82,0:08:01.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Any questions from the defense?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.45,0:08:02.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.74,0:08:13.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Masako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, when we talked before the trial,\Nyou stated that you hated the defendant.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.29,0:08:19.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why did you agree to tamper with his alibi?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.68,0:08:21.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.68,0:08:25.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm done.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.35,0:08:34.98,Signs,,0,0,0,,Tokyo Detention Center
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.31,0:08:34.56,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Hey, Usami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.52,0:08:38.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is what your wife testified in court true?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.78,0:08:50.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's strange, if you got your wife\Nto craft your alibi, why didn't you use it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.21,0:08:57.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've told you before that no matter what, to tell me the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.67,0:09:02.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, I can't continue to be your lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.18,0:09:04.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't need a lawyer anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.47,0:09:06.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.01,0:09:09.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm the one who committed the crime!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.18,0:09:13.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just hurry up and throw me into prison or whatever!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.61,0:09:23.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello, Mori's Detective Agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.82,0:09:26.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Detective Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.99,0:09:28.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, how did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.99,0:09:32.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Usami's home address is?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.87,0:09:34.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.67,0:09:38.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, is that so? I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.21,0:09:42.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks for the trouble. I'll buy you a drink later.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.59,0:09:43.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.85,0:09:48.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey Conan, I'm going out for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.47,0:09:50.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take care!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.69,0:09:59.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Hirasawa's Murder Investigation Report."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.78,0:10:01.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.53,0:10:04.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm home!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.91,0:10:06.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.24,0:10:08.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, where's Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.37,0:10:11.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.91,0:10:15.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Baby octopus was found in the victim's stomach?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.29,0:10:17.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.67,0:10:20.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, sheesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.55,0:10:25.34,Signs,,0,0,0,,Usami's Apartment
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.80,0:10:28.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, where should I begin?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.89,0:10:31.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-ji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.35,0:10:37.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,C-Conan, why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.77,0:10:42.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r} asked me to watch over you to make\Nsure you didn't get used by the prosecutor again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.32,0:10:45.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jeez, she needs to trust her own father more.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.36,0:10:48.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just don't mess anything up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.16,0:10:50.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.29,0:11:01.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This must be Masaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.38,0:11:05.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.72,0:11:09.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These are... Mimasu's matches!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.59,0:11:10.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why are they here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.85,0:11:16.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey Uncle, was there an ashtray in this room?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.43,0:11:16.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.89,0:11:19.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, I don't see one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.56,0:11:22.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Usami probably doesn't smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.90,0:11:25.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But look, there were matches sitting there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.32,0:11:30.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These are Mimasu's matches.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.95,0:11:33.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not that strange for him to have these then.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.49,0:11:36.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he was on bad terms with his ex-wife, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.45,0:11:37.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.37,0:11:40.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are different types of couples.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.79,0:11:42.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kids wouldn't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.05,0:11:46.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jeez...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.01,0:11:50.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.69,0:12:03.90,Signs,,0,0,0,,Haido Yokochou Business District
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.49,0:12:14.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, auntie.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.04,0:12:18.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you putting baby octopus in the stew today?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.37,0:12:20.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, little boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.67,0:12:24.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, it's sort of like our signature dish here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.88,0:12:25.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you like it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.13,0:12:28.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah! After all, it's really delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.51,0:12:31.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. I'll treat you some, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.34,0:12:33.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Woo-hoo! Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.51,0:12:34.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.18,0:12:39.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Auntie, you have it too, that photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.77,0:12:43.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was one in Usami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.56,0:12:45.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.69,0:12:52.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Call him as a witness again?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.28,0:12:57.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he said that he screwed up last time,\Nso he wants a chance to make up for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.74,0:13:02.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we don't have a solid alibi anymore, even if Mouri testified now...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.42,0:13:06.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whatever it is, it must have something to do with the time gap we were talking about the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.54,0:13:09.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That, and he said that if you looked at this you would know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.51,0:13:12.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These are Mimasu's matches.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.93,0:13:17.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That and one other thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.68,0:13:20.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said to look at what was inside the victim's stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.06,0:13:22.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In his stomach?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.69,0:13:24.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.21,0:13:46.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right then, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, could you please tell us about that night again?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.84,0:13:50.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At what time did you go to Mimasu?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.55,0:13:53.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The usual time, at 7:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.47,0:13:56.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when did you fall asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.97,0:13:57.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,8:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.85,0:14:05.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, you were asleep from 8:30 until 9:55, the real time when you were woken up by the phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.69,0:14:08.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess you could put it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.44,0:14:12.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is Kisaki trying to prove?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.82,0:14:15.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows, probably just going around in circles.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.82,0:14:20.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So if anything happened in the bar during that time, you wouldn't have noticed?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.20,0:14:22.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.46,0:14:29.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For example, if the defendant Usami took the victim to the store while you were asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.84,0:14:34.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Objection! This is all baseless conjecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.38,0:14:37.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I have proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.18,0:14:40.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please take a look at the victim's autopsy report.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.22,0:14:44.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the victim's stomach, something\Ncalled baby octopus was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.64,0:14:49.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is considered a signature dish at\NMimasu and is prepared regularly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.36,0:14:59.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I checked with restaurants around the area, none of them had baby octopus on their menu except for Mimasu.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.16,0:15:07.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if what the defense says is true and the victim\Nvisited the bar, what difference does it make?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.71,0:15:08.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Quite a difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.67,0:15:16.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim would have met another person with a motive to kill him besides the defendant.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.51,0:15:20.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, I was the only customer in the bar at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.76,0:15:22.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not necessarily a customer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.81,0:15:23.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.85,0:15:24.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-You don't mean...!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.31,0:15:29.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't say something stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.35,0:15:36.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mimasu's owner doing such a thing! I, Mori Kogoro, must...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.07,0:15:41.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your line of thinking is completely wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.87,0:15:43.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Dear!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.70,0:15:55.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The key to solving this case lies in what the defendant Usami and his ex-wife Masako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} truly feel for each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.67,0:16:03.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the accidental death of their beloved son, the two had grown so bitter that they divorced.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.93,0:16:14.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is the fault of that man, Hirasawa, and that night Usami met up with him and got into an argument.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.65,0:16:19.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the argument, they were kicked out of the bar at 8:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.03,0:16:25.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From there the defendant brought Hirasawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to his ex-wife's bar, Mimasu.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.83,0:16:37.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apparently, the defendant, upon encountering the man he hated for so long, didn't know what to do and took him to his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.13,0:16:41.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what happened at 8:45.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.09,0:16:49.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With Hirasawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} in front of the wife, her forgotten rage against him was rekindled.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.56,0:16:56.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From there, she first sent the defendant home, lead Hirasawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to a nearby construction site and murdered him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.44,0:17:05.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The wife hurried back to Mimasu, saw me sleeping and planned a way to create an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.24,0:17:15.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, the alibi that the prosecution saw past\Nwasn't for the defendant, but was for his wife solely.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.34,0:17:22.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As expected of you, Mr. Detective!\NA wonderful and elaborate story.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.72,0:17:28.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, this is a courtroom, not a place for you to share your clever guesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.52,0:17:30.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a place where we unveil the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.10,0:17:34.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have any objections to my theories?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.69,0:17:38.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First off, how do you know that the defendant\Nleft first, leaving the victim behind?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.73,0:17:45.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How can you be sure he didn't take the victim out after asking his wife for a made-up alibi?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.12,0:17:51.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that were the case, wouldn't the defendant have asserted his alibi from the beginning?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.37,0:17:57.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One more: how do you explain the defendant's car keys left at the crime scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.54,0:18:02.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's easy. The defendant deliberately left them near the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.63,0:18:09.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After leaving the bar alone, the defendant\Nprobably got worried and returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.02,0:18:15.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is when he witnessed Masako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} murdering Hirasawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.94,0:18:19.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps the defendant thought of it this way:
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.28,0:18:26.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rather than his wife take the blame for it, wouldn't it be better if a drunken him take it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.53,0:18:33.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And maybe he, like Hirasawa who killed their son, would have gotten off easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.37,0:18:40.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How absurd. The fact that he was drinking doesn't necessarily mean he would have gotten off lightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.75,0:18:42.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He could have been charged with a felony.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.30,0:18:46.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because he still loves his wife even now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.43,0:18:49.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He thought he still had a place in her heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.43,0:18:53.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As evidence, I have Mimasu's matches.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.43,0:18:57.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is written Mimasu in Romaji, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.60,0:18:59.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So what exactly does that prove...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.44,0:19:05.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, if you read this Romaji backwards, it is "Usami M".
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.78,0:19:10.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, their late son's name, Masaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.62,0:19:14.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The name that brought them happiness before the divorce.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.75,0:19:25.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The defendant saw these matches and realized how his wife truly felt, and so he took the blame to save her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.47,0:19:29.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a lie! I'm the one who killed him!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.05,0:19:34.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That detective is full of crap!\NI killed him with my own hands!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.77,0:19:35.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please stop, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.77,0:19:42.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all right, now I understand how you feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.19,0:19:46.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, having to testify against you like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.49,0:19:49.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't know about the keys at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.37,0:19:55.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just as Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} said, I killed Hirasawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.83,0:19:56.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Masako...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.08,0:20:02.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That man... didn't remember me at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.71,0:20:08.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sir, haven't we met somewhere before?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.84,0:20:10.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? With you, babe?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.34,0:20:17.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't remember. If I'd met a beautiful woman like you, I'd never forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.64,0:20:19.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.02,0:20:27.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't forgive him for ruining our family's happiness, and then not even remembering my face.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.95,0:20:29.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Masako...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.03,0:20:39.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how beautiful this couple's love is, a crime is a crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.67,0:20:51.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you truly love your wife, after she's paid for her sins,\Nyou'll find the strength to start over. Isn't that true love?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.68,0:22:24.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I admit defeat today. Congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.19,0:22:29.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I can't believe that the case took a turn, not because of a lawyer, but because of a witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.94,0:22:31.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a first for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.82,0:22:34.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right. A first for me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.11,0:22:37.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right then, until the next trial.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.62,0:22:39.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When that comes, please go easy on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.41,0:22:40.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Same here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.62,0:22:49.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Attorney Kisaki from now on should extend her winning streak.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.25,0:22:50.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pardon?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.38,0:22:55.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Flinging dirt on people like her, that's my job after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.01,0:23:01.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dear, thanks for everything today. I suppose I should thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.56,0:23:02.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.89,0:23:14.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The thing is, um, after this, if you have the time\Nwe could go to a restaurant and just relax...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.82,0:23:16.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Young lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.70,0:23:17.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.32,0:23:21.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's all right with you, would you like to get a bite to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.54,0:23:24.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.91,0:23:31.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it seems like he's pretty busy, so let's do\Nit another time. We're going, Kuriyama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.50,0:23:32.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.13,0:23:36.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Mom, wait a minute! Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.55,0:23:40.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad, you're impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.10,0:23:45.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez... It doesn't look like things are going to go the way Ran wants anytime soon.
